Adopting a multi-level, comparative and interdisciplinary approach, this book develops a critical analysis of policy change and welfare reform in Europe. The book applies a dynamic and change oriented perspective to shed light on policy changes that are often poorly understood in the welfare literature, and contributes to a further development of the theoretical and conceptual frameworks for understanding social change. Using citizenship as a focus, several dimensions of change are analysed simultaneously: changes in the discipline of social policy itself; the changing character of social problems; changes in social policy and citizenship; and the emergence of new forms of social integration. The book also speculates on how different dimensions of change are interlinked.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aPublic welfarezEurope. 0aWelfare statezEurope. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Services & Welfare.2bisacsh1 aAndersen, Jørgen Goul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarbier, Jean-Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorn, Asmund W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalloni, Marina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoul Andersen, Jørgen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGuillemard, Anne-Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuillemard, Anne-Marie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHalvorsen, Rune, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJensen, Per H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJensen, Per H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLarsen, Jørgen Elm, econtributor.4ctb4http